cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a federated learning architecture that enables on-device machine learning without central coordination. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper leverages blockchain to exchange and verify local learning model updates, which involves cryptographic techniques. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper proposes a distributed learning approach where mobile devices exchange model updates without relying on a central server. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper investigates the end-to-end learning completion latency of the proposed architecture, which involves analyzing the network performance. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a novel approach to federated learning that involves designing a new data structure (blockchain) to enable decentralized learning.
